extends layout

block content
  p
    | embadge.io is a simple Ember.js badge generator service.
    | It provides a simple to use API.
    |  It's inspired by Matthew Beale's
    a(href='https://github.com/mixonic/ember-community-versions') Ember Community Versions
    |  and is open-sourced
    a(href='https://github.com/halfdan/embadge.io') on Github

  h2#examples Examples
  ul
    li
      | With start version:
      br
      img(src="//embadge.io/v1/badge.svg?start=1.13.0")
    li
      | With start and end version:
      br
      img(src="//embadge.io/v1/badge.svg?start=1.13.0&end=2.0.0")
    li
      | With range:
      br
      img(src="//embadge.io/v1/badge.svg?range=^2.3.0")
    li
      | With custom label:
      br
      img(src="//embadge.io/v1/badge.svg?label=ember-cli&start=1.13.13")
    li
      | With custom label and range:
      br
      img(src="//embadge.io/v1/badge.svg?label=ember-data&range=^2.3.0")

  h2#usage Usage
  p
    | The embadge.io API supports four different parameters.
  ul
    li
      pre
        | label
      | Used to define the text label shown on the badge (default: 'ember-versions')
    li
      pre
        | start
      | Valid semver string noting the earliest supported version.
    li
      pre
        | end
      | (Optional) Valid semver string noting the last supported version.
    li
      pre
        | range
      | (Optional) Valid semver range (e.g. "^2.3.0") noting a supported range of versions. If given, <code>start</code> and <code>end</code> will be ignored.
  p
    | The API supports HTTPS and is accessed from is <code>https://embadge.io/v1/badge.svg</code>
  h3#browser Browser
  p
    | In order to easily add embadge.io to your website you can include the following script in the body:
  code
    pre
      | &lt;script src="//embadge.io/v1/badge.js" type="text/javascript"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
  p
    | This will search your page for <code>span</code> elements with the <code>embadge</code> class and use data attributes to generate the image URL.
  code
    pre
      | &lt;span class="embadge" data-start="2.3.0"&gt;&lt;span&gt;

